The paper deals with the problem of evacuating mobile agents, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The algorithms proposed in the paper involve computational techniques such as graph theory and geometric algorithms, which are relevant to the subfields of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves optimization of evacuation time, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
